1
00:00:00,458 --> 00:00:03,458
This room is the same room I told you about upstairs

2
00:00:03,958 --> 00:00:05,125
They built it recently

3
00:00:05,375 --> 00:00:09,333
In 2008 or 2010, we built this room

4
00:00:09,958 --> 00:00:11,958
Rooms became scarce because of the families

5
00:00:13,125 --> 00:00:15,625
We would come here if there was an occasion or a holiday

6
00:00:15,625 --> 00:00:17,250
Whether it was over or not, we would come here to celebrate

7
00:00:17,917 --> 00:00:21,333
Holidays and other occasions among us, this hall was enough for us

8
00:00:21,417 --> 00:00:22,750
There were also chairs

9
00:00:24,250 --> 00:00:28,458
There were only chairs, small events

10
00:00:28,708 --> 00:00:30,542
Like New Year’s and other events

11
00:00:31,042 --> 00:00:32,708
We would go out on the holiday and sit here

12
00:00:33,167 --> 00:00:36,583
Coffee and things like that, there was nothing else here

13
00:00:37,500 --> 00:00:38,833
Interviewer: Did you say there were chairs?

14
00:00:38,833 --> 00:00:40,958
Witness: Yes, there were chairs around the hall

15
00:00:42,250 --> 00:00:44,542
There was also a chair for the bishop
like the one I told you about upstairs

16
00:00:44,708 --> 00:00:46,125
The same chair was here

17
00:00:47,125 --> 00:00:49,083
Because it was larger than the one upstairs

18
00:00:49,208 --> 00:00:50,583
Up there there was more crowding, and it was up the stairs

19
00:00:51,292 --> 00:00:54,833
That was its purpose, we held small and lovely occasions

20
00:00:56,042 --> 00:00:59,250
Interviewer: What year are you talking about for this hall?

21
00:00:59,292 --> 00:01:02,542
Witness: 2010 and 2011, until ISIS arrived

22
00:01:03,625 --> 00:01:07,292
Interviewer: If we talk about the
80s and 90s , what was this place then?

23
00:01:07,958 --> 00:01:09,125
If you remember

24
00:01:09,208 --> 00:01:11,500
Witness: In the 80s and 90s, I was a student here

25
00:01:11,875 --> 00:01:14,292
I was a student here

26
00:01:15,125 --> 00:01:16,125
This place

27
00:01:16,917 --> 00:01:19,708
That room which I told you is the deacons’ room

28
00:01:19,750 --> 00:01:20,750
Opens from here

29
00:01:21,875 --> 00:01:24,500
I was a student here, I remember this place as mine

30
00:01:24,833 --> 00:01:28,417
I was a student, and my teacher’s name was Digin [Madam] Mari, may she rest in peace

31
00:01:29,167 --> 00:01:31,917
May she rest in peace, she is the one who taught me Armenian

32
00:01:32,833 --> 00:01:35,458
We sat here like in a classroom, and we were little

33
00:01:36,125 --> 00:01:38,458
We were eight or 10 years old, learning Armenian

34
00:01:39,083 --> 00:01:40,292
We would come on Fridays

35
00:01:40,542 --> 00:01:41,958
Cars would come, and they taught us

36
00:01:42,292 --> 00:01:43,292
This was a classroom

37
00:01:44,083 --> 00:01:46,292
And that is also a classroom, we will see it when we go out—there is another classroom

38
00:01:46,583 --> 00:01:48,000
It was a small classroom

39
00:01:48,500 --> 00:01:49,500
This was a classroom

40
00:01:50,958 --> 00:01:52,277
In the 80s
